modules.description: This module combines map-like operations for key-priority bindings (insertion, deletion, lookup, and priority updates) with priority queue functionality to extract minimum-priority elements and process entries within specified priority thresholds. It operates on a purely functional priority search queue storing unique keys, ordered by ascending keys for standard operations and ascending priorities for priority-based traversals. Use cases include scheduling systems requiring unique identifiers with dynamic priorities and resource management scenarios where entries must be processed based on priority thresholds.

Implements a priority search queue that maps keys to values with priorities, supporting insertion, deletion, and extraction of minimum priority entries. Works with ordered key types and prioritizes elements based on associated values. Useful for algorithms requiring efficient access to minimum-priority items, such as Dijkstra's shortest path or event-driven simulations.
